♫ <i>Leaving too many unknown colors</i> ♫

45
00:03:31,560 --> 00:03:38,199
♫ <i>Step-by-step, sinking into the vast forest of thoughts</i> ♫

46
00:03:38,199 --> 00:03:43,000
♫ <i>We meet while chasing</i> ♫

47
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:48,140
♫ <i>The stars in the dark night sky</i> ♫

48
00:03:48,140 --> 00:03:49,599
This dress looks really good on you.

49
00:03:49,600 --> 00:03:51,279
It suits you quite well.

50
00:03:52,520 --> 00:03:55,559
Does it look better on me or on Qiao Yu?

51
00:03:55,559 --> 00:03:58,179
Qiao Yu hasn't worn this dress.

52
00:03:58,179 --> 00:03:59,899
You ask me to deliver it in such a hurry,

53
00:03:59,899 --> 00:04:01,999
and you didn't even let her try it on?

54
00:04:01,999 --> 00:04:03,919
Swimming makes you extremely tired.

55
00:04:05,279 --> 00:04:07,960
Qiao Yu said both of you are into sports,

56
00:04:07,960 --> 00:04:10,379
and are quite energetic.

57
00:04:10,379 --> 00:04:12,579
I thought you'd never get tired.

58
00:04:15,119 --> 00:04:16,720
Are you jealous?

59
00:04:18,039 --> 00:04:20,060
I'm just a stand-in for Qiao Yu.

60
00:04:20,060 --> 00:04:21,979
Who am I to get jealous?

61
00:04:21,979 --> 00:04:24,159
I can smell jealousy.

62
00:04:25,359 --> 00:04:27,680
I'm just getting in the mood in advance

63
00:04:27,680 --> 00:04:32,199
and find the feeling of being pursued and liked by you.

64
00:04:32,199 --> 00:04:35,540
Yes. You should get in the mood.

65
00:04:35,540 --> 00:04:37,940
You're my Miss Right now.

66
00:04:37,940 --> 00:04:39,340
That's right.

67
00:04:39,340 --> 00:04:42,139
Your exclusive Miss Right for half a day.

68
00:04:44,959 --> 00:04:47,578
Shouldn't you remind me of anything I should pay attention to

69
00:04:47,600 --> 00:04:49,719
when having dinner with your parents?

70
00:04:49,760 --> 00:04:51,280
You know my mother pretty well.

71
00:04:51,280 --> 00:04:53,259
Just be yourself.

72
00:04:53,259 --> 00:04:56,139
She thought I'd like you one day.

73
00:04:56,139 --> 00:04:58,260
Really? Yeah.

74
00:04:58,260 --> 00:05:01,340
Haven't you found out that she was selling me out to you?

75
00:05:03,220 --> 00:05:04,720
Kind of.

76
00:05:05,519 --> 00:05:07,199
On the surface, it seemed

77
00:05:07,200 --> 00:05:09,220
that she was complaining about you with me,

78
00:05:09,220 --> 00:05:12,339
but actually, she was complimenting you.

79
00:05:14,720 --> 00:05:19,330
However, she should be more closely connected with Qiao Yu.

80
00:05:21,000 --> 00:05:23,639
You're even jealous of my mom?

81
00:05:26,079 --> 00:05:28,179
It was just a casual remark.

82
00:05:30,320 --> 00:05:31,820
What about your dad?

83
00:05:31,820 --> 00:05:34,199
Will he think it's weird for a superior and a subordinate

84
00:05:34,200 --> 00:05:36,319
to get into a relationship?

85
00:05:36,319 --> 00:05:37,919
Maybe.

86
00:05:40,040 --> 00:05:42,358
He probably thinks that I'm carrying a torch for you,

87
00:05:42,359 --> 00:05:44,060
so he won't say anything.

88
00:05:44,060 --> 00:05:46,259
Besides, my mom will be there.

89
00:05:46,259 --> 00:05:48,000
So don't worry.

90
00:05:48,000 --> 00:05:49,720
I'm not worried.

91
00:05:49,720 --> 00:05:52,759
Anyway, you'll have to clean up the mess.

92
00:06:00,880 --> 00:06:02,620
These carnations just arrived this morning.

93
00:06:02,620 --> 00:06:04,820
The colors are great.

94
00:06:04,820 --> 00:06:07,439
I'll take 12 of them, and add some baby's breath.

95
00:06:07,440 --> 00:06:08,480
Okay.

96
00:06:08,480 --> 00:06:11,500
Only 12. Will it be enough?

97
00:06:11,500 --> 00:06:13,440
How many do you want?

98
00:06:14,479 --> 00:06:16,479
12 it is then. I'll listen to my Miss Right.

99
00:06:16,479 --> 00:06:18,320
Okay.

100
00:06:18,320 --> 00:06:20,279
And six lilies, please.

101
00:06:20,279 --> 00:06:21,880
Plain packaging will do.

102
00:06:21,880 --> 00:06:23,398
I'm going to put them in a vase.

103
00:06:23,399 --> 00:06:24,820
Okay.

104
00:06:30,679 --> 00:06:32,340
Do you need anything else?

105
00:06:32,979 --> 00:06:35,299
How many colors of roses do you have?

106
00:06:35,299 --> 00:06:38,040
A lot. Which color do you like?

107
00:06:40,519 --> 00:06:42,079
Why are you looking at me?

108
00:06:42,079 --> 00:06:44,540
Buy whatever you want.

109
00:06:44,540 --> 00:06:46,259
I like them all.

110
00:06:47,220 --> 00:06:49,380
Then follow your heart.

111
00:06:50,479 --> 00:06:52,479
I'll take two for each color.

112
00:06:52,480 --> 00:06:53,839
Okay.

113
00:06:54,579 --> 00:06:56,678
Are these flowers dyed?

114
00:06:56,679 --> 00:06:58,820
No, they're all natural.

115
00:06:58,820 --> 00:07:00,359
That's good.

116
00:07:09,359 --> 00:07:11,179
Right, right.

117
00:07:11,179 --> 00:07:14,259
You're prophetic, my big writer.

118
00:07:14,259 --> 00:07:17,839
<i>Of course. I didn't write so many novels for nothing.</i>

119
00:07:18,399 --> 00:07:21,558
By the way, did you tell Lu Zhaoxi my pen name

120
00:07:21,559 --> 00:07:23,259
and he read my novels?

121
00:07:23,259 --> 00:07:27,079
No, I didn't. You didn't want me to tell others, didn't you?

122
00:07:27,079 --> 00:07:30,539
I feel it was a bit too coincidental.

123
00:07:30,539 --> 00:07:33,419
Then, how about I ask him for you?

124
00:07:33,419 --> 00:07:38,240
Never mind. I'll wait until you're really together.

125
00:07:38,240 --> 00:07:40,199
Who's going to be together with him?

126
00:07:40,200 --> 00:07:42,359
Don't you like each other?

127
00:07:43,239 --> 00:07:46,859
Who said two people who like each other have to be together?

128
00:07:46,859 --> 00:07:51,340
Yezi, I just want you to put on some airs and play it cool.

129
00:07:51,340 --> 00:07:53,979
Don't do anything stupid.

130
00:07:55,160 --> 00:07:57,419
Don't worry. I know what I'm doing.

131
00:07:57,419 --> 00:07:58,759
How can I not worry?

132
00:07:58,760 --> 00:08:01,080
I don't think you know what you're doing.

133
00:08:01,080 --> 00:08:03,879
All right. I have to hang up.

134
00:08:03,880 --> 00:08:05,259
We'll talk about it tonight.

135
00:08:05,259 --> 00:08:06,780
I...

136
00:08:09,399 --> 00:08:12,179
You didn't buy the colorful bouquet?

137
00:08:12,179 --> 00:08:15,679
I tried it and it looked so weird.

138
00:08:16,440 --> 00:08:19,258
Here you go. I prepared it especially for you.

139
00:08:20,079 --> 00:08:21,800
You prepared it for me?

140
00:08:23,679 --> 00:08:25,139
Today's my mom's birthday,

141
00:08:25,139 --> 00:08:27,500
and carnations do seem to fit her.

142
00:08:27,500 --> 00:08:31,518
But since we're here to buy flowers, my mom will scold me

143
00:08:31,519 --> 00:08:33,479
if I don't buy roses for my Miss Right.

144
00:08:33,479 --> 00:08:34,819
That makes sense.

145
00:08:34,819 --> 00:08:38,660
Buying me roses will make it look more real.

146
00:08:38,660 --> 00:08:40,158
You're so considerate.

147
00:08:40,159 --> 00:08:43,619
Of course. I've always been serious.

148
00:08:43,619 --> 00:08:46,119
- Let's go.
- Go.

149
00:08:52,559 --> 00:08:54,118
Are we going to eat at home?

150
00:08:54,119 --> 00:08:56,398
Yes. We'll cook, is that okay?

151
00:08:56,398 --> 00:08:57,900
Sure.

152
00:08:58,919 --> 00:09:01,139
Is there anything else we need to buy?

153
00:09:01,139 --> 00:09:03,519
No, I've prepared everything.

154
00:09:07,960 --> 00:09:09,320
Here.

155
00:09:11,080 --> 00:09:14,119
Hold on. I'll do it myself.

156
00:09:15,919 --> 00:09:18,140
- Give me this.
- Thank you.

157
00:09:37,139 --> 00:09:38,780
Let me help you.

158
00:09:38,780 --> 00:09:41,498
No need. Go make some tea.

159
00:09:41,498 --> 00:09:43,000
All right.

160
00:10:05,540 --> 00:10:09,019
Have you always lived loving life?

161
00:10:09,019 --> 00:10:11,220
What is loving life?

162
00:10:11,220 --> 00:10:16,059
Well, some people only want things to be practical.

163
00:10:16,059 --> 00:10:20,558
They think that the sense of form, beauty, and atmosphere

164
00:10:20,559 --> 00:10:23,141
that have a soothing effect on mind are all unimportant.

165
00:10:23,141 --> 00:10:26,259
But some people are willing to spend time and effort on them,

166
00:10:26,259 --> 00:10:28,980
and live their lives with elegance.

167
00:10:28,980 --> 00:10:31,580
- Am I like this?
- You are.

168
00:10:31,580 --> 00:10:35,398
I remember you decorated the room in Taoyuan Village with some wild flowers

169
00:10:35,398 --> 00:10:39,420
and hand-made ornaments, making it very nice and warm.

170
00:10:39,420 --> 00:10:43,819
And you suggested to put some flowers in my office.

171
00:10:43,819 --> 00:10:47,619
Even now, you're still carefully setting the table, arranging the flowers in the vase,

172
00:10:47,619 --> 00:10:49,920
and preparing a proper afternoon tea.

173
00:10:50,980 --> 00:10:53,978
I'm actually very pragmatic. You didn't find that out?

174
00:10:53,978 --> 00:10:56,419
None of these costs me money,

175
00:10:56,419 --> 00:11:00,859
or I could say they only cost very little money.

176
00:11:01,619 --> 00:11:04,240
But your time and effort are also costly.

177
00:11:04,240 --> 00:11:05,818
Even if the conditions are limited,

178
00:11:05,818 --> 00:11:10,499
you can still make your life more cozy and beautiful under limited conditions.

179
00:11:11,540 --> 00:11:13,699
I hadn't thought of it that way.

180
00:11:13,699 --> 00:11:17,219
Now that you have mentioned it, it kind of makes sense.

181
00:11:18,119 --> 00:11:22,419
In fact, I believe people are like flowers.

182
00:11:22,419 --> 00:11:28,079
Some flowers grow well in a good environment,

183
00:11:28,079 --> 00:11:32,099
having plenty of light, regular water, and enough care.

184
00:11:32,099 --> 00:11:35,319
But some flowers grow in gravel,

185
00:11:35,319 --> 00:11:38,739
without sunlight and enough water,

186
00:11:38,739 --> 00:11:42,179
they still try hard to put down roots, thrive in gravel,

187
00:11:42,179 --> 00:11:44,159
and be exposed to the sun.

188
00:11:44,159 --> 00:11:46,599
What kind of flower are you?

189
00:11:47,579 --> 00:11:51,560
I am not a flower. I'm like a leaf.

190
00:11:51,560 --> 00:11:54,580
Though it's not that delicate, pretty, and attractive,

191
00:11:54,580 --> 00:11:56,880
it's more resilient.

192
00:12:02,980 --> 00:12:07,539
If you're a leaf, I guess I probably can't see any flowers.

193
00:12:11,459 --> 00:12:13,459
You really see me as your Miss Right now?

194
00:12:13,459 --> 00:12:15,980
The honey words just came out of your mouth.

195
00:12:16,699 --> 00:12:18,599
Do you like it?

196
00:12:19,479 --> 00:12:21,220
I do.

197
00:12:21,220 --> 00:12:25,019
When your parents come, I'll surely do my best.

198
00:12:31,619 --> 00:12:33,919
Here they are. I'm going to pick them up.

199
00:12:33,919 --> 00:12:35,839
Do you want me to go with you?

200
00:12:35,839 --> 00:12:39,040
No, thanks. Just enjoy your life.

201
00:12:46,359 --> 00:12:50,939
Ye Shilan, I wasn't joking today.

202
00:13:21,220 --> 00:13:23,080
Done.

203
00:13:24,100 --> 00:13:26,580
Looks so pretty. It goes well with your outfit.

204
00:13:26,580 --> 00:13:28,598
Thank you. What do you think?

205
00:13:28,598 --> 00:13:31,280
Good. Our son has a good eye.

206
00:13:31,280 --> 00:13:34,099
Zhaoxi always has a good eye.

207
00:13:34,099 --> 00:13:37,018
Mom, Ye Shilan and I picked it out together.

208
00:13:37,018 --> 00:13:40,020
We both had our eye on it.

209
00:13:40,020 --> 00:13:42,199
You also have a good eye.

210
00:13:42,199 --> 00:13:45,958
Auntie, I have another gift for you. Please wait.

211
00:13:45,958 --> 00:13:47,779
Okay.

212
00:13:47,779 --> 00:13:49,719
Why didn't I know that?

213
00:13:49,719 --> 00:13:54,340
President, I don't think I should report this to you.

214
00:13:54,340 --> 00:13:56,400
You really don't have to.

215
00:13:57,300 --> 00:14:00,699
Auntie, this is the essential oil I made.

216
00:14:00,699 --> 00:14:03,000
You know how to make essential oils?

217
00:14:03,000 --> 00:14:06,100
I just learned it for fun. It's simple.

218
00:14:08,459 --> 00:14:10,519
Very elegant. Smell it.

219
00:14:10,519 --> 00:14:16,918
It feels like a gentle breeze from lavender fields fanned my cheek.

220
00:14:16,918 --> 00:14:19,558
You can use it at bedtime. It can help you get better sleep.

221
00:14:19,558 --> 00:14:23,059
I need it so much. I really like it. Thank you, Ye.

222
00:14:23,059 --> 00:14:25,419
I'm glad you like it, Auntie. Happy birthday.

223
00:14:25,419 --> 00:14:27,080
Thank you.

224
00:14:28,400 --> 00:14:32,660
Look. Only girls know how to give a thoughtful gift.

225
00:14:32,660 --> 00:14:36,640
Not like the two of them, they only buy me gifts in a mall.

226
00:14:36,640 --> 00:14:39,359
Mom, you can just compliment her.

227
00:14:39,359 --> 00:14:41,020
But don't depreciate our efforts.

228
00:14:41,020 --> 00:14:43,358
This is called adequate stimulus.

229
00:14:43,358 --> 00:14:47,200
Understanding your gaps can help you improve.

230
00:14:48,180 --> 00:14:49,939
I'm starving.

231
00:14:49,939 --> 00:14:51,519
Two more dishes and dinner will be ready.

232
00:14:51,519 --> 00:14:53,739
Ye Shilan, it's your turn.

233
00:14:53,739 --> 00:14:55,760
Then I'm going to cook.

234
00:15:11,039 --> 00:15:13,759
Come on. Let's toast with tea.

235
00:15:13,759 --> 00:15:14,999
Okay. Happy birthday.

236
00:15:14,999 --> 00:15:16,159
All right. Happy birthday.

237
00:15:16,159 --> 00:15:18,620
- Thanks.
- Thank you.

238
00:15:21,379 --> 00:15:23,079
- Dig in.
- Okay.

239
00:15:23,079 --> 00:15:24,760
Are you happy?

240
00:15:24,760 --> 00:15:26,980
Here, eat some more.

241
00:15:26,980 --> 00:15:28,498
This is your favorite.

242
00:15:28,498 --> 00:15:31,119
Okay, you eat some more too.

243
00:15:35,819 --> 00:15:41,440
I heard you had a little misunderstanding back in Taoyuan Village.

244
00:15:41,440 --> 00:15:45,260
Yes. At that time, I didn't know the president was changed,

245
00:15:45,260 --> 00:15:47,500
so I thought he was a liar.

246
00:15:47,500 --> 00:15:51,638
When he got back, Zhaoxi told me about this and praised you.

247
00:15:51,638 --> 00:15:54,120
Mom, don't exaggerate it.

248
00:15:54,120 --> 00:15:55,480
What did he say about me?

249
00:15:55,480 --> 00:15:57,619
He said you have a good sense of justice.

250
00:15:57,619 --> 00:15:59,519
But hot-headed.

251
00:15:59,519 --> 00:16:02,559
He said you were kind and virtuous.

252
00:16:02,559 --> 00:16:04,359
But a little aggressive.

253
00:16:04,359 --> 00:16:07,579
He said you were very pretty.

254
00:16:09,180 --> 00:16:10,980
That's true.

255
00:16:10,980 --> 00:16:14,638
You praised me, and deliberately scared me when I came back.

256
00:16:14,638 --> 00:16:16,780
That's because you felt guilty.

